abstract: >
  BabelJudge is an open-source benchmark and reliability audit framework for
  LLM-as-a-judge evaluation. It measures four systematic judge biases—position
  bias, verbosity bias, order inconsistency, and cross-lingual degradation—
  without requiring human preference labels. Gold-labeled pairwise items are
  manufactured by applying controlled perturbations to reference responses,
  making the better response known by construction. The framework extends to
  agentic settings (tool-calling and multi-turn reasoning traces) via the
  babeljudge.agentic subpackage.
